  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use is bounded to adult CPB flow rates 3–6 L/min at 2000–3500 RPM; hemolysis index is the sole QoI. Structured context-of-use fields are documented in the accompanying regulatory submission narrative rather than in this machine-readable package.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
